http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Burglars-decamp-with-gold-ornaments-in-Khammam/article13986314.ece

Burglars struck at the locked house of an LIC agent and decamped with gold and silver ornaments valued at Rs.2 lakh at BSR Nagar in Aswaraopet at around midnight on Wednesday.The incident came to light when the owner of the house returned home from a pilgrimage to a temple town along with his family members in the small hours of Thursday, sources said.They found the front door lock broken and valuables including 80 gms of gold and about one kg silver articles missing.The Aswaraopet police pressed into service the personnel of Clues Team and initiated a detailed investigation into the house-breaking incident.